      "name": "Bench-top hemolysis validation against in-vitro NIH measurements",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in-vitro measurements collected across five operating points (2.0–6.0 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM). Mean relative error was 8.3% across all operating conditions. The relative hemolysis index RH remained below 1.0 for all worst-case dimensional variants, satisfying the acceptance criterion.",
